01:17:16.527 --> 01:17:18.870
Now I figure that's
because you cut a deal.

01:17:18.871 --> 01:17:20.872
You're going to cut
another deal with me.

01:17:21.705 --> 01:17:23.143
You're going to
tell me everything.

01:17:23.144 --> 01:17:24.995
- Come on, you scum.
- No!

01:17:55.195 --> 01:17:57.204
I need to know something
about the properties of the

01:17:57.205 --> 01:17:59.506
substance you gave
Emma Craven.

01:17:59.507 --> 01:18:01.662
I would rather not discuss
it in those terms.

01:18:01.822 --> 01:18:05.337
Is it something she could have
encountered in her work?

01:18:05.338 --> 01:18:08.257
Any exposure, if there were
an exposure, would be consistent

01:18:08.258 --> 01:18:11.789
with a documentable, procedural
failure on her part.

01:18:11.790 --> 01:18:14.728
Is it something that could
have remained in her effects

01:18:14.729 --> 01:18:16.507
and been transferred to her
father without much

01:18:16.508 --> 01:18:18.624
collateral contamination?

01:18:18.659 --> 01:18:22.199
Do you mean could it have
poisoned her father as well?

01:18:23.140 --> 01:18:24.280
Yes.

01:18:26.123 --> 01:18:28.477
What, in your opinion, would
be the consequences if

01:18:28.478 --> 01:18:30.563
Craven opens his mouth?

01:18:33.696 --> 01:18:36.280
It's unsurviveable.

01:18:39.877 --> 01:18:41.762
So be it, then.

01:18:47.590 --> 01:18:49.704
Do you see a
soul in there?

01:18:49.705 --> 01:18:51.665
I beg your pardon?

01:18:52.819 --> 01:18:54.338
You can button
your shirt.

01:18:54.339 --> 01:18:56.413
You know, as we discussed
yesterday, there will be

01:18:56.448 --> 01:18:58.350
some erratic behavior.

01:18:58.351 --> 01:19:02.220
And I regret to say this probably
means you will have less time.

01:19:02.221 --> 01:19:04.219
I know what it means.

01:19:07.153 --> 01:19:09.835
I've been having
aural hallucinations.

01:19:09.836 --> 01:19:12.944
My father's voice calling
my name as I start to sleep.

01:19:14.324 --> 01:19:16.285
Bastard's been dead for
forty years and suddenly

01:19:16.286 --> 01:19:17.993
he's yelling at me again.

01:19:18.347 --> 01:19:20.985
- I come awake.
- You're not sleeping?

01:19:20.986 --> 01:19:24.288
No, I'm not sleeping, I start
to sleep, then I jolt awake.

01:19:25.869 --> 01:19:29.747
There's something
about the darkness.

01:19:29.748 --> 01:19:32.870
- I don't like it.
- I'm not a counselor.

01:19:32.871 --> 01:19:35.355
I know you want to banter
with me. I don't do that.

01:19:35.356 --> 01:19:39.983
- I can only give you the facts.
- We all know what the facts are.

01:19:40.667 --> 01:19:44.624
We live a while, and then we
die sooner than we planned.

01:19:53.158 --> 01:19:54.562
Standard procedure
with the Senator.

01:19:54.563 --> 01:19:56.318
Yeah, I get it.

01:19:57.037 --> 01:19:59.991
You know you didn't really
let the side stand with you.

01:19:59.992 --> 01:20:01.779
You got a lot of
brothers out there.

01:20:01.780 --> 01:20:04.494
Yeah, I know. But I
like a private funeral.

01:20:04.898 --> 01:20:07.341
Senator gets in his moods.
Not too good today.

01:20:07.342 --> 01:20:10.172
That's too bad. I was
jumping for joy.

01:20:15.195 --> 01:20:19.461
Are you hungry? We have
some sandwiches, a cup of tea?

01:20:20.206 --> 01:20:21.778
No thank you, Sir.

01:20:21.779 --> 01:20:25.692
Well, it's always a pleasure
to meet a combat veteran.

01:20:25.693 --> 01:20:29.463
You left as a master sergeant
of a heavy weapons platoon.

01:20:29.464 --> 01:20:30.419
Yes, Sir.

01:20:30.420 --> 01:20:35.129
- How did you do that at 20?
- Everybody else was dead.

01:20:37.761 --> 01:20:40.229
Did you have trouble adjusting
when you came home?

01:20:40.230 --> 01:20:42.054
- No.
- Really?

01:20:42.055 --> 01:20:45.488
No. People talk about
trauma and so forth.

01:20:45.489 --> 01:20:48.441
I figure you come out of
combat the way you went in.

01:20:48.442 --> 01:20:50.225
I know that's not a very
kind thing to say, but

01:20:50.226 --> 01:20:52.105
that's my observation.

01:20:52.394 --> 01:20:54.714
And I know there's a lot of
big bucks in this post traumatic

01:20:54.715 --> 01:20:59.519
stress thing. But combat is
pretty much like anything else.

01:20:59.520 --> 01:21:02.562
It helps put perspective on things
when you're scared shitless.

01:21:02.563 --> 01:21:05.150
What is the nature of our
appointment, Detective Craven?

01:21:05.151 --> 01:21:07.309
Well I was hoping that
you could tell me that.

01:21:07.310 --> 01:21:10.284
Why am I supposed to tell you
what you want to see me about?

01:21:10.285 --> 01:21:12.767
Well, because you're seeing me
in less than 48 hours after

01:21:12.802 --> 01:21:14.699
I talked to your attorney.

01:21:16.626 --> 01:21:20.985
Your daughter came to me with
allegations about Northmoor.

01:21:20.986 --> 01:21:24.568
- She sent me a letter.
- What did the letter contain?

01:21:24.569 --> 01:21:28.246
It touched on national security
matters that are classified.

01:21:30.026 --> 01:21:34.012
- What happened to the letter?
- That is also classified.

01:21:34.013 --> 01:21:38.213
But protocol would be to turn
it over to the committee that

01:21:38.214 --> 01:21:41.740
does oversight on the area your
daughters letter touched upon.

01:21:41.741 --> 01:21:43.851
Prompting an investigation
on my daughter.

01:21:43.852 --> 01:21:46.566
Opening up a DARPA file on her.
Treating her like a terrorist?

01:21:46.567 --> 01:21:49.624
I'm not involved in
security matters.

01:21:49.625 --> 01:21:52.943
I did write your daughter,
advising her she might be

01:21:52.944 --> 01:21:54.594
in breach of security.

01:21:54.595 --> 01:21:58.178
Oh. So you didn't help her?

01:21:58.939 --> 01:22:01.675
I'm glad to see you, Detective.
As both a veteran and as

01:22:01.676 --> 01:22:04.310
a police officer of your many
years of service, but I have

01:22:04.311 --> 01:22:07.120
to tell you that your daughter,
and we have to say this despite

01:22:07.121 --> 01:22:12.211
her terrible accident,
was in violation of...

01:22:12.212 --> 01:22:14.522
almost everything of which
she could be in violation.

01:22:14.523 --> 01:22:17.472
- What did she allege?
- That's classified.

01:22:18.627 --> 01:22:20.920
You know, Detective, a very
important part of Massachusetts

01:22:20.921 --> 01:22:22.923
economy is research and
development...

01:22:22.924 --> 01:22:27.642
Senator. I think you're in a
position regarding Northmoor,

01:22:27.643 --> 01:22:30.230
where you had better decide
if you're hanging on the cross

01:22:30.231 --> 01:22:33.805
or banging in the nails.
Here.

01:22:36.021 --> 01:22:38.886
These deaths are the result
of a conspiracy by one of your

01:22:38.887 --> 01:22:41.297
major campaign contributors.

01:22:42.474 --> 01:22:44.600
Why do you include your daughter?
Her death was an accident.

01:22:44.601 --> 01:22:48.110
No. She was poisoned with
cesium by Mr. Bennett.

01:22:49.975 --> 01:22:52.604
I think I'm scaring you Senator.
There's probably not too much

01:22:52.605 --> 01:22:56.062
upside to scaring a Senator, except
to provide some perspective.

01:22:56.268 --> 01:22:58.228
I'm going to go now, but I'm
going to leave you these pictures

01:22:58.229 --> 01:23:00.479
I want you to call everybody
involved, everybody concerned,

01:23:00.480 --> 01:23:02.675
and tell them I know everything
I need to know to throw a

01:23:02.676 --> 01:23:04.679
real box of Tarantulas
into this situation.

01:23:04.680 --> 01:23:05.675
- If you have info...
- Shut up!

01:23:05.676 --> 01:23:07.840
I'm not interested in
talking any more shit.

01:23:07.841 --> 01:23:09.801
You investigate this
at a national level.

01:23:09.802 --> 01:23:11.909
You do that, maybe you'll
come out of this alright.

01:23:11.910 --> 01:23:13.132
I don't know.

01:23:14.049 --> 01:23:15.342
I don't think you knew
that the people you are

01:23:15.343 --> 01:23:16.783
in business with
killed my daughter.

01:23:17.728 --> 01:23:19.551
But now that you do know...

01:23:20.060 --> 01:23:21.879
what are you going
to do about it?

01:23:22.085 --> 01:23:23.831
Good afternoon, Senator.

01:24:40.772 --> 01:24:42.654
Get out of the vehicle.

01:24:44.359 --> 01:24:46.428
What the fuck do you
think you just did?

01:24:46.429 --> 01:24:48.423
You just rear-ended an
unmarked cruiser, and I

01:24:48.424 --> 01:24:50.309
made an observation
that you are armed.

01:24:50.310 --> 01:24:51.739
Through smoked glass
and our coats?

01:24:51.740 --> 01:24:53.358
Yeah, I'm funny
that way.

01:24:53.512 --> 01:24:55.416
Get out of the car, now.
Or you're going to make

01:24:55.417 --> 01:24:56.928
a move for something on
the inside of your jackets,

01:24:56.929 --> 01:24:58.465
you understand me?

01:24:59.649 --> 01:25:01.304
Get out of the car.

01:25:06.500 --> 01:25:08.752
Alright. On your knees,
hands on your heads.

01:25:14.082 --> 01:25:15.762
- What have you got, Tom?
- These guys are armed.

01:25:15.763 --> 01:25:18.398
They were following me.
Rear-ended my car.

01:25:19.179 --> 01:25:22.281
Got some ID then?
Thanks.

01:25:25.675 --> 01:25:28.123
Not in law enforcement.
Imagine that.

01:25:29.494 --> 01:25:30.185
What are you?

01:25:30.474 --> 01:25:32.281
You don't think this is going
to get straightened out?

01:25:32.282 --> 01:25:33.828
Not for a while.

01:25:33.829 --> 01:25:36.114
These fuckers got
automatic weapons.

01:25:36.754 --> 01:25:39.413
You just made
a serious mistake.

01:25:43.095 --> 01:25:46.020
Did you shoot
my daughter?

01:25:47.629 --> 01:25:51.761
I'm the supposed target of a
killer. So you here, following me

01:25:51.762 --> 01:25:54.195
armed, with no credentials
in the city of Boston,

01:25:54.196 --> 01:25:56.184
you're out of your
fucking mind.

01:25:57.265 --> 01:25:59.237
Welcome to hell.

01:26:00.037 --> 01:26:02.677
<i>A strange new twist
in the Emma Craven case,</i>

01:26:02.678 --> 01:26:05.329
<i>a suspect has been
identified as her murderer,</i>

01:26:05.330 --> 01:26:08.353
<i>but new developments
today involving her father</i>

01:26:08.354 --> 01:26:10.861
<i>Two men have been arrested
in Boston. Police say</i>

01:26:10.862 --> 01:26:13.387
<i>the men were taken into
custody after their car</i>

01:26:13.388 --> 01:26:16.041
<i>crashed into the back
of an unmarked police car,</i>

01:26:16.042 --> 01:26:18.387
<i>driven by Boston Police
Detective Tomas Craven,</i>

01:26:18.388 --> 01:26:19.986
<i>the father of Emma Craven.</i>

01:26:19.987 --> 01:26:22.467
<i>This all happened on
Marlinton Street...</i>

01:26:29.044 --> 01:26:31.937
- Bennett.
- We need to abort right now.

01:26:31.938 --> 01:26:33.862
<i>We can't risk killing
Tom Craven yet.</i>

01:26:34.220 --> 01:26:35.699
It's too late.

01:26:35.980 --> 01:26:37.829
It's already been done.

01:26:59.880 --> 01:27:01.343
You want to try?

01:27:08.078 --> 01:27:08.900
Hold your hair back,
your mother will

01:27:08.901 --> 01:27:10.974
kill me if I get it all
messed up again.

01:27:10.975 --> 01:27:12.296
There you go.

01:27:18.887 --> 01:27:24.003
Perfect. Now a razor. Here
you go. Don't cut yourself.

01:27:24.004 --> 01:27:26.934
- Comb?
- That will work.

01:27:27.901 --> 01:27:29.053
Now watch.

01:27:47.055 --> 01:27:48.594
Painless.

01:27:48.595 --> 01:27:51.874
Wash it off.
One more.

01:28:36.211 --> 01:28:37.904
Can I come in, Tom?

01:28:40.841 --> 01:28:42.829
- You alright?
- Yeah.

01:29:02.000 --> 01:29:03.972
Do you remember when the
trooper out at the airport

01:29:03.973 --> 01:29:08.267
busted Whitey? He got
demoted and transferred.

01:29:10.737 --> 01:29:14.340
He knew what was going on.
But he couldn't prove it.

01:29:14.341 --> 01:29:16.603
And nobody wanted to
know about it.

01:29:17.246 --> 01:29:20.076
And finally he shot
himself, remember that?

01:29:22.775 --> 01:29:25.199
I don't think you'd
shoot yourself.

01:29:27.168 --> 01:29:29.553
But what's coming
is worse than that.

01:29:31.173 --> 01:29:35.779
It isn't what it is, Tommy.
It is never what it is.

01:29:35.780 --> 01:29:39.008
It is what it can be
made to look like.

01:29:41.383 --> 01:29:44.418
There's a DA in Hampshire
County, going to charge you

01:29:44.419 --> 01:29:47.126
with the death of your
daughters boyfriend.

01:29:47.416 --> 01:29:50.856
He doesn't have a case.
But that doesn't matter.

01:29:52.636 --> 01:29:56.139
It'll be five years of
people thinking you did it.

01:29:56.140 --> 01:29:58.199
You'll go broke,
you'll lose the house.

01:29:58.527 --> 01:30:00.257
And they go after
your pension.

01:30:00.258 --> 01:30:04.153
If you win the case
there'll be a civil suite

01:30:04.188 --> 01:30:05.897
by that point you won't
be able to afford a lawyer.

01:30:05.898 --> 01:30:08.155
What are they
offering you?

01:30:13.841 --> 01:30:15.992
I got kids, Tommy.

01:30:18.092 --> 01:30:19.349
I don't.

01:30:23.477 --> 01:30:25.959
But even if you did, right?

01:30:28.557 --> 01:30:32.241
- Even if you did.
- Yup. Even if I did.

01:31:21.934 --> 01:31:26.800
You know, Bill. No one
expects you to be perfect.

01:31:28.156 --> 01:31:31.414
But there's a few basic
things you got to get right.

01:31:33.723 --> 01:31:36.265
Always do the best you
can by your family,

01:31:36.266 --> 01:31:39.286
go to work every day,
always speak your mind.

01:31:39.287 --> 01:31:41.939
Never hurt anyone that
doesn't deserve it.

01:31:43.229 --> 01:31:45.660
Never take anything
from the bad guys.

01:31:47.292 --> 01:31:51.027
It's all. It's not
much to ask.

01:32:01.906 --> 01:32:03.255
Hello, Craven.

01:34:00.010 --> 01:34:01.258
I need your car.

01:34:39.455 --> 01:34:40.916
Not yet.

01:35:01.938 --> 01:35:03.186
Go ahead.

01:35:05.562 --> 01:35:06.811
Hold on.

01:35:10.022 --> 01:35:11.270
I'll call you back.

01:35:20.769 --> 01:35:22.017
Derek?

01:35:22.305 --> 01:35:23.553
Derek?

01:35:29.281 --> 01:35:30.529
Shit.

01:35:32.140 --> 01:35:33.717
You're all fucked
up, Craven.

01:35:34.331 --> 01:35:35.611
You're all done.

01:35:35.870 --> 01:35:37.275
Sit down.

01:35:37.276 --> 01:35:39.038
Lie down.

01:35:39.039 --> 01:35:40.287
Be dead.

01:35:43.421 --> 01:35:44.615
Fuck.

01:35:46.368 --> 01:35:48.637
- Say "Craven".
- Fuck you.

01:35:49.830 --> 01:35:53.347
- You fuck.
- "Craven". Say it.

01:35:54.000 --> 01:35:55.630
- Craven.
- Louder!

01:35:56.015 --> 01:35:57.264
- Craven!
- LOUDER!

01:35:57.546 --> 01:35:58.801
CRAVEN!

01:36:16.977 --> 01:36:18.618
I'm sorry you had
to see that, honey.

01:37:23.552 --> 01:37:26.014
Deep down...

01:37:26.749 --> 01:37:29.289
You know you
deserve this.

01:37:59.882 --> 01:38:02.012
We've got a cop of almost
30 years spotless service

01:38:02.013 --> 01:38:04.657
and there's not one person,
on our side, who can explain

01:38:04.692 --> 01:38:07.302
his instability without lying,
who has executed the director

01:38:07.303 --> 01:38:10.597
of a nuclear research facility
where his daughter worked.

01:38:11.706 --> 01:38:14.605
Okay. Ideas?

01:38:20.981 --> 01:38:23.320
Your scenario is this.

01:38:23.614 --> 01:38:26.952
He was accidently
poisoned by his daughter.

01:38:30.010 --> 01:38:32.816
- But he blamed Bennett.
- How do we know that?

01:38:32.817 --> 01:38:37.230
Testimony of an altercation at
Northmoor when he was there.

01:38:37.231 --> 01:38:38.864
Testimony from the Senator.

01:38:38.865 --> 01:38:42.116
I can easily testify that he was
unstable. He came to my house.

01:38:42.117 --> 01:38:46.421
That's right. He made wild
allegations. He was armed.

01:38:46.422 --> 01:38:48.775
You know, you were
very lucky to live.

01:38:48.776 --> 01:38:50.451
That's true.
That's very true.

01:38:50.452 --> 01:38:53.161
Now the real story
here gentlemen, is:

01:38:53.162 --> 01:38:56.810
"United States Senator
escapes assassination."

01:38:56.845 --> 01:38:58.464
- That's right.
- That's the lead story.

01:38:58.465 --> 01:39:00.107
That will wipe the rest of
it right out of the media.

01:39:00.108 --> 01:39:02.302
Anyone who looks
at the rest of this

01:39:02.303 --> 01:39:04.825
is going to see that
something happened.

01:39:04.826 --> 01:39:07.233
But no one is going to be
able to figure it out.

01:39:07.234 --> 01:39:08.796
That's your objective.

01:39:08.797 --> 01:39:12.755
To make it so convoluted that
anyone can have a theory.

01:39:12.756 --> 01:39:16.172
- But no one’s got the facts.
- That's quite good, Jedburgh.

01:39:16.173 --> 01:39:20.238
Senator, I've been making things
unintelligible for 30 years.

01:39:20.670 --> 01:39:24.495
And by the way, its
Captain Jedburgh to you.

01:39:24.976 --> 01:39:27.781
Captain. Of what?

01:39:30.357 --> 01:39:32.273
Very little he can
tell you about.

01:39:35.056 --> 01:39:38.265
Right. Well. Seems we
have a good starting point.

01:39:38.266 --> 01:39:40.423
What's the prognosis
on Craven?

01:39:40.424 --> 01:39:44.508
- Well, you know he's terminal.
- We're all terminal, Millroy.

01:39:44.509 --> 01:39:46.506
Even middle management.

01:39:46.507 --> 01:39:48.242
But how fast is
he being terminal?

01:39:48.243 --> 01:39:51.492
- He's incapable of speech.
- Thank God for that.

01:39:57.365 --> 01:39:59.724
I understand you had a chance
to terminate Detective Craven

01:39:59.725 --> 01:40:01.433
and did not do so.

01:40:01.703 --> 01:40:06.891
You come to me. I look
at things. I decide.

01:40:06.892 --> 01:40:10.143
Jedburgh, we've got to get
the Senator out to the press.

01:40:12.887 --> 01:40:15.243
I've decided what
this country is.

01:40:16.018 --> 01:40:17.059
What?

01:40:18.214 --> 01:40:21.398
People, who
deserve better.

01:40:22.459 --> 01:40:25.649
We all appreciate Captain Jedburgh.
Yet we would have not got

01:40:25.650 --> 01:40:28.819
to this extremity had he done what
the situation clearly dictated.

01:40:28.820 --> 01:40:31.902
Senator, I don’t think you
really understand what side

01:40:31.903 --> 01:40:34.039
of this situation you're on.

01:40:39.898 --> 01:40:42.207
Well, I think we've had
a successful meeting...

01:40:49.183 --> 01:40:50.960
I...

01:40:50.961 --> 01:40:53.994
am a United
States Senator.

01:40:54.614 --> 01:40:55.930
By what standards?

01:41:09.064 --> 01:41:12.274
- You got a family?
- Yeah.

01:41:12.647 --> 01:41:14.916
- Kids?
- Yeah.

